, and Michael Raiger offer more focused approaches to writers as varied as Gerard Manley Hopkins, Katherine Lee Bates, Flannery O'Connor, Wallace Stevens, T.S. Eliot, and Seamus Heaney and to special genres like spritual autobiography and film.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 17. Dez 2021) 7aRELIGION / Christianity / General.2bisacsh1 aAnderson, John M., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aAnglen, Kevin Van, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aAppleyard, J. A., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBarth, J. Robert, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBoyd, John, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFix, Stephen, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGates, Henry Louis, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHall, Dorothy Judd, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKearney, Richard, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKiely, Robert, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLeigh, David, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMahoney, John L., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aPonder, Melinda, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aRaiger, Michael, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aRule, Philip C., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aRzepka, Charles J., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aRzepka, Jane R., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aTaylor, Dennis, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/c